                   InterACTIVE Digital Devices Presents:
               AMIGA Smart Port(TM) Analog Upgrade Version 1.0
                   for F-15 Strike Eagle II By MicroProse

                      Upgrade written by Alvin Derouen





-------------------------------INSTALLATION-----------------------------------
NOTE: The default ICONS are designed for WorkBench 2.0. WorkBench 1.3 ICONS are
      also included. They have "For1.3" appended to the normal name. Just
      rename and copy over the normal one to use. (All this will do is make the
      the icons look better , there are no other differences.)


                                 HARD DISC
 Move the F15 II Upgrade to the directory in which F15 II resides.
 This may be accomplished by either:
  A. CLI:
     Insert the original "SmartPortCal" disk in a floppy drive.
     Copy "F15 II Upgrade" and "F15 II Upgrade.info" to the hard disk directory
     that holds F15 II.
  B. Workbench:
     Insert the original "SmartPortCal" disk in a floppy drive.
     Open the directory "Analog Upgrades" on the "SmartPortCal" disk. Open the
     directory inside the "Analog Upgrades" window named "F15 Strike Eagle II".
     Now Open the directory on the hard disk that holds "F15 II".(it should be
     called F15II). Next use the mouse to move the "F15 II Upgrade" icon and
     drop it into the hard disk window.
     (You may have to rearrange the windows to do this)


                                   FLOPPY
 Move the F15 II Upgrade to the "f15ii(game)" disk (That is the name of the
 original disk).
             WARNING: use a copy , DO NOT use the original!!!
 This may be accomplished by either:
  A. CLI:
     Insert the original "SmartPortCal" disk in a floppy drive.
     Insert a COPY of the original "f15ii(game)" disk in a floppy drive.
     (That is the name of the F15 II disk.)
     DO NOT USE THE ORIGINAL DISK!!! Copy the "F15 II Upgrade" program and
     "F15 II Upgrade.info" to the "f15ii(game)" disk.
  B. Workbench:
     Insert the original "SmartPortCal" disk in a floppy drive.
     Open the directory "Analog Upgrades" on the "SmartPortCal" disk. Open the
     directory inside the "Analog Upgrades" window named "F15 Strike Eagle II".
     Insert a COPY of the original "f15ii(game)" disk in a floppy drive.
     (That is the name of the F15 II game disc)
     DO NOT USE THE ORIGINAL DISK!!!  Now double click on the "f15ii(game)"
     icon to  open up a window for the game disk. Next, use the mouse to move
     the "F15 II Upgrade" icon from the "F15 Strike Eagle II" window and drop
     it into the "f15ii(game)" window.
     (You may have to rearrange the windows to do this)


---------------------------------- LOADING -----------------------------------
 WARNING: For hard disk use, the game MUST have been installed properly before
          this Upgrade will work. (Including the assigns!)

 Just click on the Icon from the workbench , or from the cli, run the file
 "F15 II Upgrade". (With quotes)


  NOTE: You may also run the Upgrade without installing it. Double click on the
        "F15 II Upgrade" icon on the original disk. You will then be
         prompted to insert "f15ii(game):". After the disk is inserted, it
         will load normally.


  NOTE: This Upgrade does not in any way change the original program. You MUST
        run the program each time by useing the IDD upgrade. If you do not ,
        none of the new features will operate.




--------------------------------- NEW FEATURES --------------------------------
ALL of the following NEW features for F15 Strike Eagle II are now available
using the Amiga Smart Port from IDD!
 1. More sensitive control!  The F-15 upgrade makes use of the full range
    (0-251) of the AMIGA Smart Port instead of the original limited range
    provided by the game. (0-40)

---------------------------------- OPERATION -----------------------------------
IMPORTANT: The analog joystick will NOT work correctly, if the light labeled
           "PC1" on the AMIGA Smart Port is not on. Press the "Fire" button
           to activate the "PC1" light and switch to analog mode.

To use the analog joystick, just pick it from the start-up menu.





